{"timestamp":"2026-02-13T00:23:55.740Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"item_completed","thread_id":"019c545e-1980-76d2-b8c1-42d1549d6ea8","turn_id":"019c545f-3507-79d2-9b6c-2ef92ffb2a06","item":{"type":"Plan","id":"019c545f-3507-79d2-9b6c-2ef92ffb2a06-plan","text":"# Cadence CLI v0.2.0 Output + UX Refresh\n\n## Summary\nUpdate the CLI to v0.2.0, adopt `console`, `dialoguer`, and `indicatif` only where they add value, and redesign user-facing output to be clean, cargo‑style, and non-technical enough to be comfortable while still transparent about what’s happening. Remove “INFO/WARNING/ERROR” language entirely and fix existing clippy warnings.\n\n## Key Changes\n1. **Version bump**\n   - Update `Cargo.toml` version to `0.2.0`.\n   - Regenerate `Cargo.lock` after dependency changes.\n\n2. **New dependencies**\n   - Add:\n     - `console` for styling and terminal-friendly output.\n     - `dialoguer` for interactive prompts in `gpg setup`.\n     - `indicatif` for progress in hydrate scans.\n   - Keep usage minimal and scoped to user-facing UX.\n\n3. **Output formatting (cargo-style, user-facing)**\n   - Introduce a small `ui` module (new `src/ui.rs`) that:\n     - Formats action lines like: `cadence  Installing hooks`\n     - Supports `action`, `note`, `success`, `fail`, and `detail` helpers.\n     - Uses `console::style` for color only when the output is a TTY.\n   - Replace raw `eprintln!(\"[cadence] ...\")` logs in:\n     - `src/main.rs`\n     - `src/push.rs`\n   - Remove all “warning:”/“error:”/“INFO”‑style labels.\n   - Keep technical details (like `elapsed_ms`, hash refs, or command names) but write them in human language:\n     - Example: “Could not read session log (…); skipping”\n     - Example: “Sync complete (elapsed 214ms)”\n\n4. **Dialoguer for yes/no and input**\n   - Use `dialoguer::Input` and `dialoguer::Confirm` in `gpg setup` for real interactive sessions.\n   - Preserve testability by keeping a non‑TTY fallback prompter that uses the current buffered reader/writer logic.\n   - Refactor:\n     - Create a `Prompter` trait with `input()` and `confirm()`.\n     - Implement `DialoguerPrompter` (interactive) and `BufferedPrompter` (tests).\n     - Update `run_gpg_setup()` to use `DialoguerPrompter`.\n     - Update `run_gpg_setup_inner()` to accept a prompter and preserve test behavior.\n\n5. **Indicatif progress**\n   - Add a spinner or progress bar in `run_hydrate()`:\n     - Spinner for “Scanning agent logs…”\n     - Optional bar for “Processing N session logs” once count is known.\n   - Ensure the progress output does not pollute non‑TTY output (disable or fall back to plain text when not interactive).\n\n6. **Clippy fixes**\n   - Apply the `collapsible_if` simplifications in:\n     - `src/push.rs` (hash compare)\n     - `src/main.rs` (`hook_command_exe` and `debug_hook_exe_path`)\n\n7. **Tests updated**\n   - Update any assertions on output strings to match the new format:\n     - Status output text (e.g., `Auto-push` line).\n     - GPG setup/status outputs if strings change (no “error:” wording).\n   - Keep GPG prompt helper unit tests intact via the buffered prompter.\n\n## Public Interfaces / Behavior Changes\n- CLI output format will change (user-facing UX improvement).\n- Interactive GPG setup uses dialoguer when TTY is available.\n- No change to CLI flags, command structure, or note content format.\n\n## Test Plan\n- `cargo test`\n- `cargo check`\n- `cargo clippy`\n\n## Assumptions / Defaults\n- Cargo-style output will use `cadence` prefix and a short action word (e.g., `Installing`, `Syncing`, `Done`, `Failed`).\n- No interactive prompts are added to hook flows; autopush consent remains non-interactive to avoid blocking git hooks.\n- ANSI colors are enabled only for TTY output; plain text otherwise.\n"}}}
